      • executeTask

        public static boolean executeTask(Task task,
                                  JTaskConfig config)
        Executes the specified task in a new thread, and automatically pops open a JTask UI Component for visually monitoring the task.

        This method will block until the JTask UI Component is disposed. Disposal will occur automatically if JTaskConfig is set to setAutoDispose(true). Otherwise, disposal will occur when the user manually closes the JTask UI Dialog Box.

        Parameters:
        task - the task to execute.
        config - Configuration options for the JTask UI Component.
        Returns:
        true value indicates that task completed successfully. false value indicates that task was halted by user or task encountered an error.
